{
  "paths": {
    "beersmith": "/Users/YOUR_USERNAME/Library/Application Support/BeerSmith3",
    "uv": "/Users/YOUR_USERNAME/.local/bin/uv"
  },
  "grocy": {
    "url": "http://localhost:9283",
    "api_key": "your-grocy-api-key-here"
  },
  "currency": {
    "default": "GBP",
    "beersmith": "GBP",
    "grocy": "GBP",
    "exchange_rates": {
      "USD": 0.79,
      "EUR": 0.86,
      "CAD": 0.58,
      "AUD": 0.51
    }
  },
  "units": {
    "default_weight": "kg"
  },
  "notes": [
    "SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:",
    "",
    "1. Copy this file to config.json:",
    "   cp config.example.json config.json",
    "",
    "2. Update paths.beersmith with your BeerSmith 3 data directory:",
    "   macOS: /Users/YOUR_USERNAME/Library/Application Support/BeerSmith3",
    "   Windows: C:\\Users\\YOUR_USERNAME\\Documents\\BeerSmith3",
    "   Linux: /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.beersmith3",
    "",
    "3. Update paths.uv with your uv executable path:",
    "   macOS/Linux: which uv",
    "   Windows: (Get-Command uv).Source",
    "",
    "4. Update grocy.url and grocy.api_key:",
    "   - Get API key from Grocy: Settings > Manage API keys",
    "   - URL format: http://localhost:9283 or http://192.168.x.x:9283",
    "",
    "5. Update currency settings:",
    "   - Query Grocy currency: get_system_config() tool",
    "   - Update exchange_rates if using multiple currencies",
    "",
    "6. NEVER commit config.json (it contains your API key!)",
    "   - It's in .gitignore for security",
    "   - Keep config.example.json updated instead",
    "",
    "For more details, see docs/CONFIG.md"
  ]
}
